title: The evaluation of the photonuclear reaction cross sections using the method of reduction at significant systematic uncertainties.

x4freetext: The evaluation  of  the  photonuclear  reaction  cross
sections using the method of reduction at significant
systematic uncertainties.

x4freetext: English translation of YK,,(1),52,1993.
The method based on the method of reduction is
proposed for  the  evaluation  of  the   photonuclear
reaction cross   sections   have   been  obtained  at
significant systematic    uncertainties    (different
apparatus functions,  calibration  and  normalization
uncertainties).
The main criterium used in  analysis was similarity of
the generalized features of initial  cross  sections,
such  as  integrated  cross  sections  and centres of
gravity,  to their  weighted-mean  values.  The  main
principle   used   for   analyzing  and  reducing  of
systematic  discrepancies  between  the   results  of
different   experiments   was   some   transformation
(recalibration- correction of  the  scale  in  energy
axis,  renormalization-correction  of  the  scale  in
cross section axis)  of  initial  cross sections with
that  aim   of   forming   the   best   agreement  of
generalized characteristics.
Initial cross sections whose generalized features were
too different  from  the  weighted-mean  values  (the
systematic  errors  were  too high) were rejected and
the entire procedure was repeated.
The set  of cross section values  that  have satisfied
all the selection criteria,  was used to evaluate the
cross sections and their errors by means of reduction
method.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Mean root-square errors are given.
By V.V.Varlamov.
The  evaluation  method  consists  of using  the  real
apparatus function  (effective  photon  spectrum)  of
each  individual  experiment  to reduce the data to a
representation generated by an apparatus function  of
better   quality.   The  most  reasonably  achievable
monoenergetic representation of the information about
cross   section  contained  in  different  experiment
observables was founded with taking into account  the
experimental   uncertainties   of   calibration   and
normalization procedures.

The total photonuclear cross section (gamma,xn) =
((gamma,n) + (gamma,n+p) + 2 (gamma,2n)  +  ...)  was
evaluated but the threshold of reaction (gamma,n+p)is
23.0 MeV and that of reaction (gamma,2n) - 28.9 MeV.
